  ✒ Description:
      The ADAPTIVE ICON definition (Android 8.0+/API 26 = the "v26"). It pairs a background layer + a foreground layer; the launcher masks them into the device's icon shape. mipmap (not drawable) is the launcher-icon convention.

  ✒ Key Features:
      - Background layer bound to @color/ic_launcher_background (navy).
      - Foreground layer bound to @mipmap/ic_launcher_foreground (the custom vault mark).
      - Density-independent: the anydpi-v26 qualifier lets the launcher composite and mask at any density.

  ✒ Other Important Information:
      XML forbids double-hyphen sequences inside comments and AAPT2 hard-fails on them, so this header closes with a box-drawing rule instead of the Kotlin nine-hyphen rule. Legacy pre-API-26 launchers fall back to the rasterized mipmap-*/ic_launcher.png assets.
  ─────────
-->
<adaptive-icon xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android">
    <background android:drawable="@color/ic_launcher_background" />
    <foreground android:drawable="@mipmap/ic_launcher_foreground" />
</adaptive-icon>
